{"type":"message","id":"74a167bd","parentId":"152c6813","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:20:50.334Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h6zv052azg4u_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5276\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2951\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] experiment\r\n[mutation proposed] experiment\r\n[master 868a55b] pulse: 2026-03-24 122016\n 6 files changed, 374 insertions(+), 99 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 122016.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 122016.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 121914.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 122016 - The CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants have CFI<0.7 (noise/metaprogramming artifacts), yet current compression is frequency-based only. No implementation exists yet for CFI-weighted compression comparison.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"tidy-harbor","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5276\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2951\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] experiment\r\n[mutation proposed] experiment\r\n[master 868a55b] pulse: 2026-03-24 122016\n 6 files changed, 374 insertions(+), 99 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 122016.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 122016.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 121914.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 122016 - The CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants have CFI<0.7 (noise/metaprogramming artifacts), yet current compression is frequency-based only. No implementation exists yet for CFI-weighted compression comparison.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774369250331}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b62fba2","parentId":"74a167bd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:20:50.336Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h6zv052azg4u_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 121914\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_EXPERIMENT_SPEC.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n2. Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n3. CFI Analysis completed - found that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0), only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7)\r\n\r\nThe pending actions include:\r\n- CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n- Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n- Distinguish \"constant format\" (freq=60, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<60, CFI>0.7)\r\n\r\nThe key insight from the session is that CFI analysis revealed two types of persistence:\r\n1. Process (CFI=0, metaprogramming artifacts) - should be filtered out\r\n2. Research Trajectory (CFI>0.7, causal) - the true signal\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action would be to start the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This involves:\r\n1. Creating a method to weight tokens/phrases by their CFI score\r\n2. Comparing prediction accuracy vs the frequency baseline\r\n\r\nBut first, I need to understand what data exists. Let me check if there's any raw pulse data or frequency analysis that can be used for the experiment.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the notes, there's a file `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` that was created. I should look at what data is available there and what the experiment should look like.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete experiment design that advances toward the CFI-weighted compression experiment goal. I should create a document that outlines:\r\n1. The experiment methodology\r\n2. How to compare CFI-weighted vs frequency baseline\r\n3. What data sources to use\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete action that advances the pending goal.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants are either noise (CFI=0) or low-signal (CFI<0.7), while only 5.7% are true causal anchors. A CFI-weighted compression experiment is the natural next step to validate this finding against prediction quality.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nDesign and document the CFI-weighted compression experiment methodology, specifying how to compare CFI-weighted token selection against frequency-only baseline for next-pulse prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment Design\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** Draft - pending implementation\r\n\r\n## Objective\r\nValidate that CFI-weighted compression produces better next-pulse prediction than frequency-only baseline.\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nTokens with CFI >= 0.7 (true causal anchors) will yield better next-pulse prediction accuracy than tokens selected purely by frequency, even if frequency-selected tokens are more common.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Data Sources\r\n- Pulse history: `pulse_*.md` files in root\r\n- CFI results: `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\r\n- Frequency invariants: derived from pulse history token counts\r\n\r\n### Baseline: Frequency-Only Selection\r\n1. Count token frequencies across all pulse files\r\n2. Select top-K most frequent tokens (K = compression budget, e.g., 500)\r\n3. Use these as \"memory\" for next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\n### Test: CFI-Weighted Selection\r\n1. Calculate CFI for each token/invariant\r\n2. Filter to CFI >= 0.7 (true causal anchors)\r\n3. If count < K, fill with next-highest CFI tokens\r\n4. Use these as \"memory\" for next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\n### Prediction Task\r\nGiven selected tokens as context, predict:\r\n- Key topics in next pulse\r\n- Architectural decisions likely to be discussed\r\n- Pending actions likely to be advanced\r\n\r\n### Success Metrics\r\n- Topic overlap score (Jaccard similarity)\r\n- Action coherence (predicted actions match actual)\r\n- CFI-weighted > frequency-only on majority of metrics\r\n\r\n## Implementation Steps\r\n1. Extract all tokens from pulse_*.md files\r\n2. Calculate frequency distribution\r\n3. Calculate CFI scores (reuse method from CFI_RESULTS.md)\r\n4. Implement selection functions (baseline vs CFI-weighted)\r\n5. Run prediction comparison\r\n6. Document results\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nCFI-weighted selection will capture ~5.7% of tokens but represent >50% of meaningful prediction signal. Frequency baseline will have more tokens but mostly metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0).\r\n\r\n## Related\r\n- `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` - CFI analysis foundation\r\n- `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md` - gap as compression theory\r\n- Pulse script: `pulse.ps1`\r\nfile: research/CFI_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:19:37\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774369250334}}
